It also proposes a new pooling method that captures richer statistics of deep features. 

It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new method for improving the representation and generalization abilities of deep CNNs, which is a common goal in machine learning research. 

The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a new method for improving the performance of deep CNNs, which is a common task in artificial intelligence research. 

The paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a new pooling method that is based on the geometry of covariances, which is a common approach in neural network research. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it focuses on improving the performance of deep CNNs for image classification tasks.
